 Then we desire to call the Chyrurgeons that 
view'd and opened the Body, Mr. Skillard , and Mr. Cambridge ;
both whom were Sworn.

 Here is a great Circumstance my Lord. I asked    
her what Clothes he was in when he came to Sir Edmondbury's ; 
and she saith, the same that he hath now.

 Do you remember you were sent of a message 
from the Queens-Head at Bow , and whether? Pray tell my Lord, 
and the Jury.
